author: chuck
msg: Proxy module moved to modules/proxy. Its dependencies in Makefile.tmpl are
now handled in its own Makefile. This sets up to be out of the way of future
main source dir changes, and reorganize the proxy, splitting the massive
source file, fixing things, and moving towards a real protocol handler

author: chuck
msg: It gets rid of the type= stuff (although it should still work -- netscape
just doesn't provide that).  It also will do an NLST if the RETR fails
(indicating that it might be a directory and not a file), and it uses a
new function (show_dir) that hacks the NLST data to provide links to the
files and directories that are returned.
